\subtree{
\title{Scripts}
\p{Use these Python automation tools for version management, recipe queries, and code generation:}

\p{\strong{Version Detection & Reference Loading:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/get_references.py\stopverb} - Detect user's Zig version and return correct reference path (use this first)}
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/detect_version.py\stopverb} - Standalone version detection with confidence levels}
}

\p{\strong{Recipe Queries:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/query_recipes.py\stopverb} - Search and filter recipes by topic, tag, difficulty, or keyword}
}

\p{\strong{Code Generation:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb scripts/code_generator.py\stopverb} - Generate Zig code from JSON specifications}
}

\p{\strong{When to execute vs reference:}}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Execute} \code{\startverb get_references.py\stopverb} at the start of any Zig task to determine the correct reference path}
\li{\strong{Execute} \code{\startverb query_recipes.py\stopverb} when searching for practical code examples or solutions}
\li{\strong{Reference} other scripts only when the user explicitly requests code generation or version management tasks}
\li{Most scripts are for skill maintenance, not routine usage}
}

\p{See \code{\startverb scripts/README.md\stopverb} for complete script documentation.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflows}
\subtree{
\title{Writing New Code}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Start from template} - Copy appropriate template from \code{\startverb assets/templates/\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Check version} - Default to Zig 0.15.2 unless specified}
\li{\strong{Handle errors explicitly} - Use \code{\startverb try\stopverb}, \code{\startverb catch\stopverb}, or \code{\startverb errdefer\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Pass allocators} - Never use global state, pass allocators as parameters}
\li{\strong{Add tests immediately} - Write \code{\startverb test\stopverb} blocks alongside implementation}
\li{\strong{Document public APIs} - Use \code{\startverb ///\stopverb} doc comments for exported functions}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Debugging Compilation Errors}
\p{\strong{Zig-specific gotchas:}}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Comptime type resolution} → Use \code{\startverb @TypeOf()\stopverb} inspection or add explicit casts}
\li{\strong{Allocator lifetime issues} → Verify \code{\startverb defer\stopverb} cleanup order and \code{\startverb errdefer\stopverb} on error paths}
\li{\strong{Optional unwrapping} → Use \code{\startverb .?\stopverb} only when certain; prefer \code{\startverb orelse\stopverb} or \code{\startverb if\stopverb} unwrap for safety}
}

\p{\strong{Debug tools:} \code{\startverb std.debug.print()\stopverb} for inspection, \code{\startverb -Doptimize=Debug\stopverb} for stack traces, \code{\startverb zig test\stopverb} to isolate issues}
}

\subtree{
\title{Explaining Concepts}
\p{To teach Zig concepts effectively:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Load relevant reference} - Start with the appropriate reference file for the topic}
\li{\strong{Show runnable code} - Use complete examples from \code{\startverb examples/\stopverb} directory}
\li{\strong{Highlight uniqueness} - Emphasize Zig's distinguishing features (explicit allocators, comptime, no hidden control flow)}
\li{\strong{Reference stdlib} - Point to specific standard library functions when applicable}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Version Awareness}
\p{\strong{Default to Zig 0.15.2} unless user specifies otherwise or detection determines a different version.}

\subtree{
\title{Version Detection Workflow}
\p{At the start of any Zig task, determine the user's version using this workflow:}

\p{\strong{1. Check for explicit specification:}}

\ul{
\li{User stated version in current conversation ("I'm using Zig 0.13")}
\li{CLAUDE.md project file contains Zig version specification}
\li{\code{\startverb build.zig.zon\stopverb} has \code{\startverb minimum_zig_version\stopverb} field}
}

\p{\strong{2. Automated detection (recommended):}}

\pre{\startverb
# Run get_references.py to detect version and get correct reference path
python scripts/get_references.py --json
\stopverb}

\p{This script:}

\ul{
\li{Runs \code{\startverb scripts/detect_version.py\stopverb} to analyze the project}
\li{Attempts \code{\startverb zig version\stopverb} command (most reliable)}
\li{Scans \code{\startverb build.zig\stopverb} and \code{\startverb .zig\stopverb} files for version markers}
\li{Returns reference path and version info with confidence level}
\li{Handles fallbacks automatically (e.g., 0.14.1 → use 0.15.2 refs)}
}

\p{\strong{3. Manual detection (if automated fails):}}

\ul{
\li{Scan \code{\startverb build.zig\stopverb} for API patterns:}
\li{\code{\startverb b.path(...)\stopverb} → 0.11+}
\li{\code{\startverb std.Build\stopverb} → 0.11+}
\li{\code{\startverb b.addExecutable(.{...})\stopverb} → 0.11+}
\li{\code{\startverb b.addExecutable("name", "file")\stopverb} → pre-0.11}
\li{Check \code{\startverb .zig\stopverb} files for syntax markers:}
\li{\code{\startverb for (items, 0..) |item, i|\stopverb} → 0.13+}
\li{\code{\startverb async\stopverb}/\code{\startverb await\stopverb} keywords → 0.9-0.10 (removed in 0.11)}
\li{Load \code{\startverb references/version-differences.md\stopverb} for full detection markers}
}

\p{\strong{4. Ask user if ambiguous:}}

\ul{
\li{"I detected you might be using Zig 0.13+ based on your build.zig. Can you confirm your version?"}
\li{Offer common versions: 0.15.2 (stable), 0.14.1, 0.13.0, master (development)}
}

\p{\strong{5. Default to 0.15.2:}}

\ul{
\li{Use current stable if no detection succeeds}
\li{Inform user: "Assuming Zig 0.15.2. Let me know if you're using a different version."}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Loading Version-Specific References}
\p{\strong{After detecting version:}}

\ol{
\li{Use \code{\startverb scripts/get_references.py\stopverb} to determine correct reference path}
\li{Load references from that version directory (e.g., \code{\startverb references/v0.15.2/\stopverb})}
\li{Always load \code{\startverb references/version-differences.md\stopverb} (shared file) for migration guidance}
}

\p{\strong{Example workflow:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Detect version and get reference path
REF_PATH=$(python scripts/get_references.py)
# REF_PATH is now "references/v0.15.2" or "references/latest"

# Load version-specific documentation
cat $REF_PATH/core-language.md
cat $REF_PATH/build-system.md

# Version differences is shared across all versions
cat references/version-differences.md
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Handling fallbacks:}}

\ul{
\li{If exact version not available (e.g., 0.14.1), script returns closest match (0.15.2) with warning}
\li{Warnings indicate major differences (e.g., "for loop syntax differs from 0.13+")}
\li{Always check fallback warnings to understand version compatibility}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Critical Breaking Changes}
\p{Be aware of these major version differences when writing code:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{0.11+}: Async/await removed, new build.zig API (\code{\startverb std.Build\stopverb}, \code{\startverb b.path()\stopverb})}
\li{\strong{0.13+}: Modern for loop syntax (\code{\startverb for (items, 0..) |item, i|\stopverb})}
\li{\strong{0.12-}: Different for loop syntax (manual index variables)}
\li{\strong{Pre-0.11}: Legacy build API (\code{\startverb std.build.Builder\stopverb}), different error sets}
}

\p{\strong{See \code{\startverb references/version-differences.md\stopverb} for:}}

\ul{
\li{Detailed migration guides (0.10→0.11, 0.12→0.13, 0.13→0.15)}
\li{Error message translations}
\li{Before/after code examples}
\li{Breaking changes catalog}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Handling Different Versions}
\p{\strong{When user specifies or detection determines a different version:}}

\ol{
\li{Run \code{\startverb scripts/get_references.py --version <VERSION>\stopverb} to get correct reference path}
\li{Load \code{\startverb references/version-differences.md\stopverb} for migration details}
\li{Use version-specific references from the returned path}
\li{Adapt code patterns to the user's version}
\li{Flag deprecated features if using older version}
\li{Recommend modern alternatives when possible}
}

\p{\strong{Best practice for cross-version code:}}

\ul{
\li{Prefer feature detection over version checks: \code{\startverb @hasDecl(std, "Build")\stopverb} instead of \code{\startverb if (version >= 0.11)\stopverb}}
\li{See \code{\startverb references/latest/patterns-integration.md\stopverb} for \code{\startverb @hasDecl\stopverb}/\code{\startverb @hasField\stopverb} examples}
\li{Document target version in code comments: \code{\startverb // Target Zig Version: 0.15.2\stopverb}}
\li{For cross-version templates, see \code{\startverb assets/templates/cross-version/\stopverb}}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices}
\p{Core Zig idioms:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Explicit error handling} - Use \code{\startverb try\stopverb}, \code{\startverb catch\stopverb}, or error unions; never ignore errors}
\li{\strong{Defer cleanup} - Use \code{\startverb defer\stopverb} for cleanup, \code{\startverb errdefer\stopverb} for error-path cleanup}
\li{\strong{Pass allocators} - Never use global state; pass allocators explicitly as parameters}
\li{\strong{Leverage comptime} - Use compile-time execution for generic programming}
\li{\strong{Write tests inline} - Use \code{\startverb test "description" {}\stopverb} blocks alongside implementation}
\li{\strong{Document public APIs} - Add \code{\startverb ///\stopverb} doc comments for exported functions}
\li{\strong{Handle optionals explicitly} - Use \code{\startverb orelse\stopverb}, \code{\startverb .?\stopverb}, or \code{\startverb if\stopverb} unwrapping}
\li{\strong{No hidden control flow} - Zig has no hidden allocations, exceptions, or async}
}
}
}